TabContentProxyImpl
public abstract class ProxyPlaceImpl<P extends Presenter>
extends PresenterProxyImpl<P>
implements ProxyPlace

A proxy with a place represents a particular 'bookmark' or location inside the application. A place is stateful - it may represent a location with it's current settings, such as a particular ID value, or other unique indicators that will allow a user to track back to that location later, either via a browser bookmark, or by clicking the 'back' button.

Author:
David Peterson, Philippe Beaudoin

public ProxyPlaceImpl(EventBus eventBus,
                      PlaceManager placeManager,

Creates a ProxyPlace for a Presenter that is attached to a Place. That is, this presenter can be invoked by setting its a history token that matches its name token in the URL bar.

onBind

public void onBind()
Description copied from class: HandlerContainer
Important : Make sure you call your parent class onBind().

This method is called when binding the object. Any event handlers should be initialised here rather than in the constructor. Other costly initialisation should be done here too, in order to speed-up construction.

Handlers registered by calling (HandlerRegistration) will be removed automatically. Any other initialisation that takes place here (or as a side-effect of what is done here) should be taken down in HandlerContainer.unbind().

This method will never be invoked more then once, or if it is, the second time will necessarily be preceded by an invocation of HandlerContainer.unbind().

Overrides:
onBind in class HandlerContainer

Requests the presenter to reveal itself on screen. Upon being revealed presenters will ask to be inserted within their parent presenters by firing a SetContentEvent which will cause the parent to be revealed too.

Specified by:

canReveal

public boolean canReveal()
Description copied from interface: ProxyPlace
Checks if the associated presenter can be revealed.

The default implementation of this method always return true, but subclasses should override this and check to make sure the current user has the privileges to see the place. Make sure the places you request in PlaceManager.revealDefaultPlace() and PlaceManager.revealErrorPlace(String) can reveal themselves, otherwise your application could get into an infinite loop.

Specified by:
canReveal in interface ProxyPlace
Returns:
true if the presenter can be revealed, false otherwise.
